{"data":{"post":{"id":"af7b45d7-36d5-51a4-955d-fc7f02325aea","fileAbsolutePath":"/Users/varya/WebDev/Personal/varya.github.com/content/posts/patterned-triangle/index_en.md","html":"<p>As you might know, I recently run the <a href=\"https://github.com/toivonen/bem-love\">BEM\nLOVE</a> project to demonstrate how blocks\ncan communicate with JavaScript.<excerpt/></p>\n<p>The first example is dull enough; <a href=\"http://toivonen.github.com/bem-love/desktop.bundles/ask-her-what-music-she-likes/ask-her-what-music-she-likes.html\">a boy, a girl and the heartless\nworld</a>.</p>\n<p>Today, I was going to start with another one with a boy plunging into\ndifficulties of choice. He has <a href=\"http://toivonen.github.com/bem-love/desktop.bundles/choose-the-one/choose-the-one.html\">two girls to\nask</a>.\nSuddenly there is a <strong>challenge for you</strong>.</p>\n<p>Let’s think if it’s possible to attract a boy with a booooooring one-colour\ndress? Seems like no.<br/>\nSo, the girls in the page are in need of nice patterned dresses. Any ideas on\nhow to code a patterned triangle in CSS?</p>\n<h3 id=\"where-to-code\"><a href=\"#where-to-code\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Where to code?</h3>\n<p>To dress the girls excellenty and toppingly you need just three steps:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fork the project and <a href=\"https://github.com/toivonen/bem-love#how-to-contribute\">run the\nserver</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/toivonen/bem-love/tree/master/desktop.bundles/choose-the-one/blocks/girl/_dressed\">Contribute to modifiers</a></li>\n<li>Make your pull request</li>\n</ul>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As you might know, I recently run the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/toivonen/bem-love"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"BEM\nLOVE"}]},{"type":"text","value":" project to demonstrate how blocks\ncan communicate with JavaScript."},{"type":"element","tagName":"excerpt","properties":{},"children":[]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The first example is dull enough; "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://toivonen.github.com/bem-love/desktop.bundles/ask-her-what-music-she-likes/ask-her-what-music-she-likes.html"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"a boy, a girl and the heartless\nworld"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Today, I was going to start with another one with a boy plunging into\ndifficulties of choice. He has "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://toivonen.github.com/bem-love/desktop.bundles/choose-the-one/choose-the-one.html"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"two girls to\nask"}]},{"type":"text","value":".\nSuddenly there is a "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"challenge for you"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Let’s think if it’s possible to attract a boy with a booooooring one-colour\ndress? Seems like no."},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nSo, the girls in the page are in need of nice patterned dresses. Any ideas on\nhow to code a patterned triang